I"ó	<p>The <code>discogs</code> platform allows you to see the current amount of records in your <a href="https://www.discogs.com">Discogs</a> collection.</p>
<h2>Setup</h2>
<p>First, youâ€™ll need to get a personal access token from your Discogs account.
You can generate a token from your profileâ€™s <a href="https://www.discogs.com/settings/developers">Developer settings</a>.</p>
<h2>Configuration</h2>
<p>To enable this sensor, add the following lines to your <code>configuration.yaml</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Example configuration.yaml entry
sensor:
  - platform: discogs
    token: YOUR_TOKEN
</code></pre>
<p>The monitored conditions can create a sensor which displays the amount of records currently in your collection and/or wantlist, and an option to pick a random record from your collection.</p>
